Abstract = {{The evolution of Smart City projects is pushing researchers and
   companies to develop more efficient embedded hardware and also more
   efficient communication technologies. These communication technologies
   are the focus of this work, presenting a new routing algorithm based on
   dynamically-allocated sub-networks and node roles. Among these features,
   our algorithm presents a fast set-up time, a reduced overhead and a
   hierarchical organization, which allows for the application of complex
   management techniques. This work presents a routing algorithm based on a
   dynamically-allocated hierarchical clustering, which uses the link
   quality indicator as a reference parameter, maximizing the network
   coverage and minimizing the control message overhead and the convergence
   time. The present work based its test scenario and analysis in the
   density measure, considered as a node degree. The routing algorithm is
   compared with some of the most well known routing algorithms for
