   cities. In this context, this paper presents an optimization operation
   technique for Building Energy Management Systems (BEMS), using control
   monitor-based Building Information Modeling (BIM) for the efficient
   operation of the EOC. BIM is one of the approaches that can be used for
   the visual representation, management, and exchange of information on
   all aspects of a building. The EOC should be able to efficiently
   represent the data from the building information, and the operator
   maintaining it should be able to promptly acquire the data for handling
