Month = {{APR}},
Abstract = {{Cities are complex environments in which digital technologies are more
   and more pervasive; this digitization of the urban space has led to a
   rich ecosystem of data producers and data consumers. Moreover,
   heterogeneous sources differ in terms of data complexity,
   spatio-temporal resolution and curation/maintenance costs. Do those
   diverse urban sources reflect the same picture of the city? Do distinct
   perspectives share some commonalities?
