   holistic, integrated, and multidisciplinary approach to the concept of
   smart cities. Smart cities are evolving by the creation of tools that
   are application specific; therefore, European classification of smart
   city applications will be reviewed (as authors have used these criteria
   to classify the analyzed applications) and the relationship between the
   different European smart classification standards are analyzed.
   Moreover, in order to see how reality aligns with the theoretical
   concept of smart cities, the authors analyzed 61 applications from 33
   smart cities distributed in North America, South America, Europe and
   Asia. From these, 16 specific applications from eight cities have been
