Abstract = {{This paper discusses the utilisation of PV systems for electric vehicles
   charging for transportation requirements of smart cities. The gap
   between PV power output and vehicles charging demand is highly variable.
   Therefore, there is a need for additional support from a public
   distribution grid or a storage device in order to handle the residual
   power. Long term measurement data retrieved from a charging station for
   15 vehicles equipped with a PV system were used in the research. Low and
   high irradiation seasons influenced the PV output. The charging demand
   of electric vehicles varied over the course of a year and was correlated
   to weather conditions. Therefore, the sizing and performance of a
   supportive storage device should be evaluated in a statistical manner
