   paper focuses on the potentials of a resource-saving, sustainable
   transport system with reduced, but still satisfactory, mobility. To
   achieve the vision of resource-efficiency in Europe, a new understanding
   of mobility is needed: ``the mode of travel is the reward of the
   journey{''}, meaning that it is not about travelling fastest and
   frequently, but unhurried (easy-going), infrequently and sustainably. We
