Volume = {{63}},
Number = {{4}},
Pages = {{897-905}},
Month = {{DEC}},
Abstract = {{For 3D object localization and tracking with multiple cameras the camera
   poses have to be known within a high precision. The paper evaluates
   camera pose estimation via a fundamental matrix and via the known object
   in environment of multiple static cameras. A special feature point
   extraction technique based on LED (Light Emitting Diodes) point
   detection and matching has been developed for this purpose. LED point
   detection has been solved searching local maximums in images and LED
   point matching has been solved involving patterned time functions for
   each light source. Emitting LEDs have been used as sources of known
   reference points instead of typically used feature point extractors like
   ORB, SIFT, SURF etc. In such a way the robustness of pose estimation has
   been obtained. Camera pose estimation is significant for object
   localization using the networks with multiple cameras which are going to
   an play increasingly important role in modern Smart Cities environments.}},
