   type to type, etc. Generally, buildings are classified into residential,
   commercial and industrial. This study is aimed to distinguish the types
   of residential buildings in Singapore and establish a mathematical model
   to represent and model the load profile of each type. Modeling household
   energy consumption is the first step in exploring the possible demand
   response and load reduction opportunities under the smart grid
   initiative. Residential electricity load profiling includes the details
   on the electrical appliances, its energy requirement, and consumption
   pattern. The model is generated with a bottom-up load model. Simulation
   is performed for daily load profiles of 1 or 2 rooms, 3 rooms, 4 rooms
